									<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
										<tr>
											<td width="100%" valign="top">					
												<!-- START NEWS AREAS-->
												<table width="90%" border="0" align="center" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
													<tr><td valign="top" width="100%">&nbsp;<br>
													<!-- strMainData goes here-->
													<table width='100%' cellpadding='3' border='0'>
<tr>
<td vAlign='absmiddle' align='left' width='80%' colSpan='4' bgcolor='#000000' class='header'><img border='0' src='./images/cricon.gif' align='absmiddle'> SOULFIRE</td>
</tr>
<tr> 
<td width='80%'><p><b>Chapter 1 :&nbsp;</b>Kalatrina
Plossen is one of the greatest Paladins in the Land. Her duty is to train new,
young knights and keep an eye on the Hated Freeport Militia. She can be found at
the Hall of Truth in North Freeport. She is directly above the entrance on the
second floor. When you Hail her, she informs you she has need of young knights.
After further investigation, you learn of a spy within the Militia. He is in
danger and Kalatrina hands you a note to give to him. He can be found in the
Freeport Militia House.</p>
<p><b>Chapter 2 : </b>The beginnings of your Quest! Rush over to the Militia House. The spy
is in the middle of the Militia House in the Courtyard on the first floor. You
give him the code and he warns you of danger. You hand him the note. Suddenly,
Militia swarm to the spy and begin attacking him! He hands you an old piece of
burned parchment and yells to return to the Hall of Truth. He falls to the Evil
Guards. Run to the Hall of Truth! Upon further inspection of the note you read:&nbsp;Zimel's
Blades with some prices. Give the note to Kalatrina.</p>
<p><b>Chapter 3 : </b>Kalatrina is excited by the note you have been given. Do <u>not</u>&nbsp;give
Kalatrina Plossen the Note. If you do, restart the Quest and get it again. This
is where the Quest is counter-intuitive. If you give her the Note, she tells you
Zimel was a great Blacksmith who knew the secret of enchanting blades and making
superior weapons. This is a bug in the Quest.&nbsp; Do <u>not</u> give her the note and
carry it with you.&nbsp; She tells you to go and talk to Rashinda Elore at the
Office of the People. Rashinda is difficult to get any information out of but
once you do, you determine that Groflah Steadirt of Groflah's Forge, was a
friend of Zimel's and may have more information. When you ask Rashinda of
Zimel's Blades, Lakeen Boorheez wanders in, saying he is lost. He quickly exits
and heads to the tunnels.</p>
<p><b>Chapter 4 :&nbsp;</b>Run
over to Groflah's Forge and ask him about Zimel. He is on the second floor of
the Forge and is not very helpful. He is nervous when you ask him of Zimel and
tells you he will not speak here. Hand Groflah the Note you received from the
Spy. Groflah tells you many things and asks you to meet him at the Seafarer's
Roost. He can study the Note and try to decode the information. Groflah hands
you the Note back.</p>
<p><b>Chapter 5 :&nbsp;&nbsp;</b>Wandering
over to the Seafarer's Roost, buy a drink, relax and watch Freeport go about its
business. Groflah <i>should</i>&nbsp;show up between 1am and 3am. When he arrives, ask
who Zimel is. He will go into a long story about how Zimel has disappeared and
the Blade, Soulfire has been lost. Hand Groflah the Note and he attempt to
decipher it. Groflah tells you that he thinks Sir Lucan D'Lere, Head of the
Freeport Militia, and Pietro Zarn, Head of the ShadowKnight Guild in Freeport
are in cahoots and searching for Soulfire as well.</p>
<p><b>Chapter 6 : </b>Thanking
him for his knowledge, look about the Seafarer's Roost. Who is wandering around?
A&nbsp;beggar named Tykar Renlin should be close by. Asking Tykar for
information about Zimel, Tykar responds by saying he is thirsty. Purchase a
Drom's Champagne from the Bartender and give one to Tykar. Repeat this three
more times. Tykar informs you that Zimel has been thrown into Prison by the
Militia near the Arena. Feeling guilty, Tykar hands you a blanket to give to
Zimel if you should meet him.</p>
<p><b>Chapter 7 :&nbsp;</b>Alas!
It is true! Zimel is locked in a cell and has been driven crazy. After asking
Zimel various questions, he responds by saying he wants some items. After
deciphering his unintelligible speech, you determine he wants Bog Juice, Edible
Goo and a Blanket. Well, Tykar gave you the Blanket. You have seen Edible Goo in
the various Bakeries and know it is the most basic of delicacies. Bog Juice,
wait! You know a Brewer who has the recipe and seem to recall even drinking some
before! Hand each of these items to Zimel. Zimel will give you a key simply
marked H.K.102</p>
<p><b>Chapter 8 : </b>H.K.102? 'tis a Chest key. Ah! In Highhold Pass, Humans have built a
bank there to guard their riches from the barbaric Orcs and Gnolls. Visit the
bank in Highhold Pass and hand the Bank Clerk the key. She thanks you for the
key and hands you a Note to deliver to Brother Hayle. Alas, she is certain he is
being held captive in a cell in Splitpaw, a Gnoll stronghold.</p>
<p><b>Chapter 9 : </b>Journeying
into Splitpaw, you find Brother Hayle and hand him the Note. Brother Hayle hands
you the Note once again and asks you to retrieve a number of items for him. He
would like you to prove your nobility to him. He asks you to bring the Hilt of
Soulfire back to him. The Hilt is being held by an Evil ShadowKnight named
Xicotl in MistMoore Castle! As well, bring him the Brilliant Sword of Faith
(Quest info <a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/pon/articledetails.asp?id=47">here</a>).
Finally, he asks you to bring your Testimony (Quest info <a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/pon/articledetails.asp?id=48">here</a>).</p>
<p><b>Chapter 10&nbsp;:&nbsp;</b>You
have destroyed and defeated many Evil Creatures that wander Norrath. You have
lived up to your name and go back to Brother Hayle, truly bringing proof of your
Nobility. Brother Hayle will thank you and grant you one of the greatest blades in the
land! Soulfire!</p></td>
</tr>
